com.fasterxml.storemate.shared.hash

Class IncrementalHasher32

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fasterxml.storemate.shared.hash.IncrementalHasher32
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    IncrementalMurmur3Hasher

    public abstract class IncrementalHasher32
extends Object
    Base class for hashers that can work in incremental fashion, that is, where content is sent via one or more calls to update(byte[], int, int), before final hash value is calculated.

    Note: implementations are required to retain state so that it is possible to calculate "partial" hash values throughout content, and call calculateHash() multiple times, at different points. This is different from many other hash calculation abstractions.

      • calculateHash

        public abstract int calculateHash()
        Method for completing calculation of the hash value for the full byte sequence fed with update(byte[], int, int). This will NOT reset state, so it is completely legal to feed more content with update(byte[], int, int), and calculate further hash codes with same instance.

        NOTE: since no state is reset with a call, calling this method typically results in calculation to finalize state. So if you need to access same hash value multiple times, call this method once and retain hash value.
